The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: India will begin their Asia Cup campaign against Bangladesh on June 16 at Dambulla, which is the venue for the meet. Defending champions and hosts Sri Lanka kick off proceedings in the June 15-24 event when they take on Pakistan in the tournament opener on June 15. As per the schedule released by Sri Lanka Cricket, six matches will be played in the league phase before the June 24 final at Dambulla.    
	The Schedule    
	June 15: Sri Lanka vs Pakistan; June 16: India vs Bangladesh; June 17: Reserve Day; June 18: Sri Lanka vs Bangladesh; June 19: Pakistan vs India; June 20: Reserve Day; June 21: Pakistan vs Bangladesh; June 22: India vs Sri Lanka; June 23: Reserve Day; June 24: Final; June 25: Reserve Day.        
	Panaji: Former India wicketkeeper and chief selector Kiran More Thursday suggested that state-level cricket academies be strengthened so that they can deliver the goods instead of relying on the National Cricket Academy. More was speaking at a seminar on the future of Indian cricket organised by the Sports Journalists Federation of India.        
	London: Christopher Martin-Jenkins has been appointed as the new president of the MCC. The former cricket writer and radio broadcaster will begin his one-year term on October 1 when he takes over from former Sussex captain John Barclay.       
	Bopanna up  
	New Delhi: Rohan Bopanna and Aisam-ul Haq Qureshi rallied to beat fourth seeds Colin Fleming and Ken Skupski 2-6, 6-3, 10-5 to book a berth in the doubles quarter final of the ATP Estoril Open in Portugal.  
	Randhir view  
	New Delhi: The IOA secretary general Randhir Singh Thursday said that the government has failed to understand the Olympic Charter and should have consulted the IOC before issuing the regulation to limit the tenures of sports administrators.      
	Margao: Salgaocar edged past Mumbai FC by a solitary goal in their 24th round I-league encounter at the Nehru Stadium on Thursday.                                                                                                                                                       
